## Repost with Caption (Quote Repost) - Implementation Plan

### 1. Database Schema Changes

**Approach: Add columns to the existing `journals` table** (following the `is_remix` / `remix_source_journal_id` precedent).

Add three new columns to the `journals` table:

```sql
ALTER TABLE journals
  ADD COLUMN is_repost BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE,
  ADD COLUMN repost_source_journal_id UUID REFERENCES journals(id) ON DELETE SET NULL,
  ADD COLUMN repost_caption TEXT;
```

**Column rationale:**
- `is_repost` (boolean, default false) -- Flag to identify repost journals in queries. Mirrors the `is_remix` pattern.
- `repost_source_journal_id` (UUID, nullable FK to journals.id, ON DELETE SET NULL) -- Points to the **original source** post. Using SET NULL rather than CASCADE so the repost survives even if the original is deleted. This allows showing a "this post has been deleted" placeholder.
- `repost_caption` (text, nullable) -- The plain text caption the reposter writes. Max 280 characters enforced at application level.

**Add a unique constraint to prevent duplicate reposts:**
```sql
ALTER TABLE journals
  ADD CONSTRAINT unique_user_repost
  UNIQUE (user_id, repost_source_journal_id)
  WHERE is_repost = TRUE;
```

Note: Supabase/PostgreSQL supports partial unique indexes. If the `WHERE` clause is unsupported via the Supabase dashboard, create it as a partial unique index instead:
```sql
CREATE UNIQUE INDEX idx_unique_user_repost
  ON journals (user_id, repost_source_journal_id)
  WHERE is_repost = TRUE;
```

**Notification type:** Add `'repost'` as a new type value in the `notifications` table's `type` column (which is already a text column, so no schema change is needed -- just a new string value).

### 2. Backend Implementation

#### 2a. New Service: `repostService` in `server/services/interactService.js`

Add a new exported function `repostService` at the bottom of `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\server\services\interactService.js`. This follows the same file pattern as `likeService`, `addCommentService`, etc.

```javascript
export const repostService = async (sourceJournalId, caption, userId) => {
    // 1. Validate inputs
    if (!sourceJournalId) {
        throw { status: 400, error: 'sourceJournalId is required' };
    }
    if (!userId) {
        throw { status: 400, error: 'userId is required' };
    }

    const trimmedCaption = typeof caption === 'string' ? caption.trim() : '';
    if (trimmedCaption.length > 280) {
        throw { status: 400, error: 'caption must be 280 characters or less' };
    }

    // 2. Fetch the source journal to validate it exists, is public, and get owner
    const { data: sourceJournal, error: sourceError } = await supabase
        .from('journals')
        .select('id, user_id, title, content, post_type, canvas_doc, privacy, is_repost, repost_source_journal_id')
        .eq('id', sourceJournalId)
        .maybeSingle();

    if (sourceError) {
        throw { status: 500, error: 'error fetching source journal' };
    }
    if (!sourceJournal) {
        throw { status: 404, error: 'source journal not found' };
    }
    if (sourceJournal.privacy !== 'public') {
        throw { status: 403, error: 'cannot repost a private post' };
    }

    // 3. Self-repost prevention
    if (sourceJournal.user_id === userId) {
        throw { status: 400, error: 'cannot repost your own post' };
    }

    // 4. If reposting a repost, follow the chain to the original
    let ultimateSourceId = sourceJournal.id;
    let ultimateSourceOwnerId = sourceJournal.user_id;
    if (sourceJournal.is_repost && sourceJournal.repost_source_journal_id) {
        const { data: originalJournal, error: origError } = await supabase
            .from('journals')
            .select('id, user_id, privacy')
            .eq('id', sourceJournal.repost_source_journal_id)
            .maybeSingle();

        if (!origError && originalJournal && originalJournal.privacy === 'public') {
            ultimateSourceId = originalJournal.id;
            ultimateSourceOwnerId = originalJournal.user_id;
        }
        // If original is gone or private, fall back to the repost itself as source
    }

    // 5. Check for duplicate repost (user already reposted this source)
    const { data: existingRepost, error: existingError } = await supabase
        .from('journals')
        .select('id')
        .eq('user_id', userId)
        .eq('repost_source_journal_id', ultimateSourceId)
        .eq('is_repost', true)
        .maybeSingle();

    if (existingError) {
        throw { status: 500, error: 'error checking existing repost' };
    }
    if (existingRepost) {
        throw { status: 409, error: 'you have already reposted this post' };
    }

    // 6. Insert the repost journal entry
    // Reposts don't need embeddings or universe coordinates -- they're lightweight
    const repostTitle = `Repost: ${sourceJournal.title || 'Untitled'}`.slice(0, 180);
    const repostPayload = {
        user_id: userId,
        title: repostTitle,
        content: null,
        canvas_doc: null,
        post_type: 'repost',
        is_repost: true,
        repost_source_journal_id: ultimateSourceId,
        repost_caption: trimmedCaption || null,
        privacy: 'public',
    };

    const { data: insertedRepost, error: insertError } = await supabase
        .from('journals')
        .insert(repostPayload)
        .select('id, created_at')
        .single();

    if (insertError) {
        // Handle missing column fallback (same pattern as canvas remix)
        const isMissingColumn = insertError.message?.includes('is_repost')
            || insertError.message?.includes('repost_source_journal_id')
            || insertError.message?.includes('repost_caption');
        if (isMissingColumn) {
            throw { status: 500, error: 'repost columns not yet added to database' };
        }
        throw { status: 500, error: 'error creating repost' };
    }

    // 7. Send notification to original author (skip if self)
    const notifyUserId = ultimateSourceOwnerId;
    if (notifyUserId !== userId) {
        await supabase
            .from('notifications')
            .insert({
                sender_id: userId,
                receiver_id: notifyUserId,
                journal_id: ultimateSourceId,
                type: 'repost',
                read: false,
            });
    }

    return {
        message: 'repost created',
        repostId: insertedRepost.id,
        sourceJournalId: ultimateSourceId,
    };
};
```

**Key design decisions:**
- `post_type: 'repost'` -- This gives a distinct type so the feed query can distinguish reposts from text/canvas posts. This is better than reusing 'text' because reposts have no real content/canvas_doc of their own.
- No embeddings -- Reposts are not original content, so they don't need vector embeddings or universe placement. This keeps the operation fast.
- `ON DELETE SET NULL` on the FK -- If the original post is deleted, `repost_source_journal_id` becomes null, and the frontend shows a "deleted post" placeholder.

